        <updateDate>2025-07-25T16:12:43Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improving Access to Medicare Coverage Act of &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill deems an individual receiving outpatient observation services in a hospital as an inpatient for purposes of satisfying the three-day inpatient hospital-stay requirement&amp;nbsp;with respect to&amp;nbsp;Medicare coverage of skilled nursing facility (SNF) services. (Generally, individuals must have been an inpatient at a hospital for at least three days in order to qualify for SNF services. An individual's time spent under observation at a hospital for purposes of determining whether the individual should be admitted does not count towards this requirement.)&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
